(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)t
300 1215 M
(Issue Number:  17-001)t
300 1255 M
(Title:         Header Inclusion Policy)t
300 1295 M
(Section:       17.3.4.1  [)t
898 1295 M
(lib.res.on.headers])t
300 1335 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 1375 M
(Description:)t
300 1455 M
(The \(original\) header inclusion policy of allowing any C++ header to include)t
300 1495 M
(any other C++ header creates portability problems for users.  For example, the)t
300 1535 M
(following might compile correctly with some implementations and fail with)t
300 1575 M
(others:)t
450 1655 M
(#include <string>  // programmer meant to write <)t
1577 1655 M
(iostream>)t
450 1695 M
(using namespace std;)t
450 1735 M
(int main\(\) {)t
450 1775 M
(   )t
519 1775 M
(cout << "Hello, C++ World" << )t
1209 1775 M
(endl;)t
450 1815 M
(   return 0;)t
450 1855 M
(   })t
300 1935 M
(The \(current\) header inclusion policy of specifying exactly which C++ headers)t
300 1975 M
(include which other C++ headers causes difficulty for )t
1542 1975 M
(implementors.  The worst)t
300 2015 M
(case is when one header requires reference to another but the other is not)t
300 2055 M
(specified as included.  Another troublesome case occurs when the)t
300 2095 M
(implementation of one header \(like <complex>\) could benefit from access to)t
300 2135 M
(something in another header \(like template )t
1289 2135 M
(numeric_limits in <limits>\).)t
300 2215 M
(The LWG has discussed these problems at length, and explored several)t
300 2255 M
(alternatives including )t
829 2255 M
(implementor's namespaces \(rejected because they don't)t
300 2295 M
(allow template )t
645 2295 M
(specializations by users\).  The approach discussed in Santa)t
300 2335 M
(Cruz is to:)t
450 2415 M
(-- Put more effort into correcting the synopsis lists of required)t
450 2455 M
(header #includes.  Sensible inclusion minimizes both )t
1669 2455 M
(implementor's and)t
450 2495 M
(user's problems.)t
450 2575 M
(-- Continue to require inclusion of headers listed in synopsis, but)t
450 2615 M
(also allow inclusion of names from other headers.  This allows a user)t
450 2655 M
(to write portable programs \(by only relying on names from the required)t
450 2695 M
(headers\), allows automatic diagnosis of non-portable programs, and yet)t
450 2735 M
(also gives )t
703 2735 M
(implementor's access to names they want and need.)t
300 2815 M
(Resolution:)t
300 2895 M
(   Change the Working Paper as follows:)t
showpage
